{"session_id": 43, "bill_id": 11441, "bill_type": "Senate Bill", "bill_number": 5, "bill_title": "provide immunity for qualified mental health professionals at appropriate regional facilities.", "sponsors": [{"legislator_profile_id": 1672, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1706, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1734, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1662, "is_prime": false}], "keywords": ["Civil Commitment", "Liability", "Mentally Ill Persons"], "audio": [{"meeting_datetime": "2020-02-05T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SHE", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2020/she14.mp3", "start_seconds": 502.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2020-02-05T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SHE", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2020/she14.mp3", "start_seconds": 502.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2020-02-05T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SHE", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2020/she14.mp3", "start_seconds": 502.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2020-02-05T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "SHE", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2020/she14.mp3", "start_seconds": 502.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2020-03-02T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2020/hju29.mp3", "start_seconds": 2810.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2020-03-02T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2020/hju29.mp3", "start_seconds": 2810.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2020-03-02T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HJU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2020/hju29.mp3", "start_seconds": 2810.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 11441, "bill_version_id": 61814, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2020-01-09T18:37:57.96-06:00", "bill_text": "An Act to provide immunity for qualified mental health professionals at appropriate regional facilities. Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of South Dakota: Section 1. That \u00a7 27A-10-23 be AMENDED: 27A-10-23. Immunity from liability--Mobile crisis referral--Exception. Any law enforcement officer or authority, or any qualified mental health professional in a clinic or, hospital, or appropriate regional facility, who in good faith transferred direct supervision of a person to a mobile crisis team or a crisis intervention team certified law enforcement officer, is immune from any civil liability for such referral. Any member of a mobile crisis team or a crisis intervention team certified law enforcement officer, whose actions, in the supervision, examination, or placement of a person in compliance with this section and \u00a7\u00a7 27A-10-20 to 27A-10-22, inclusive, are taken in good faith, are immune from any civil liability for the referral, supervision, examination, transfer, or placement of the person. The immunity from civil liability under this section and \u00a7\u00a7 27A-10-20 to 27A-10-22, inclusive, does not apply if injury results from gross negligence or willful or wanton misconduct. Any law enforcement officer or authority who acts in compliance with subsection 27A-10-21(2)(b) and \u00a7 34-20A-57 is not criminally or civilly liable for the officer's or authority's actions."}, {"bill_id": 11441, "bill_version_id": 69294, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2020-03-03T16:21:53.077-06:00", "bill_text": "ENTITLED An Act to provide immunity for qualified mental health professionals at appropriate regional facilities. Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of South Dakota: Section 1. That \u00a7 27A-10-23 be AMENDED: 27A-10-23. Immunity from liability--Mobile crisis referral--Exception. Any law enforcement officer or authority, or any qualified mental health professional in a clinic, hospital, or appropriate regional facility, who in good faith transferred direct supervision of a person to a mobile crisis team or a crisis intervention team certified law enforcement officer, is immune from any civil liability for such referral. Any member of a mobile crisis team or a crisis intervention team certified law enforcement officer, whose actions, in the supervision, examination, or placement of a person in compliance with this section and \u00a7\u00a7 27A-10-20 to 27A-10-22, inclusive, are taken in good faith, are immune from any civil liability for the referral, supervision, examination, transfer, or placement of the person. The immunity from civil liability under this section and \u00a7\u00a7 27A-10-20 to 27A-10-22, inclusive, does not apply if injury results from gross negligence or willful or wanton misconduct. Any law enforcement officer or authority who acts in compliance with subsection 27A-10-21(2)(b) and \u00a7 34-20A-57 is not criminally or civilly liable for the officer's or authority's actions. An Act to provide immunity for qualified mental health professionals at appropriate regional facilities. I certify that the attached Act originated in the: Senate as Bill No. 5 Secretary of the Senate President of the Senate Attest: Secretary of the Senate Speaker of the House Attest: Chief Clerk Senate Bill No. 5 File No. ____ Chapter No. ______ Received at this Executive Office this _____ day of _____________, 2020 at ____________M. By for the Governor The attached Act is hereby approved this ________ day of ______________, A.D., 2020 Governor STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA, ss. Office of the Secretary of State Filed ____________, 2020 at _________ o'clock __M. Secretary of State By Asst. Secretary of State"}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 11441, "action_date": "2020-01-14T12:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 61791, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/61791.pdf", "status_text": "First read in Senate and referred to", "journal_page": 10, "committee_id_action": 447, "committee_id_assigned": 457, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 11441, "action_date": "2020-01-29T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 63951, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/63951.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for hear